name: MaCaw Hall (Seattle Opera/Pacific Northwest Ballet)
directions: One the main floor behind the staircase near the restaurant between men's and women's. On all floors on the right side between men's and women's.
comment: Only accessible when there is a performance, open 2 hours to showtime, all day if there is a matinee and evening show. Main floor no ticket needed, must go through the restaurant area. Upper floors ticket required.

name: Science Museum

comment: Entrance to the museum is free

name: British Motor Museum - Showroom

name: William Howard Doane Library
directions: First floor in the stacks (sort of open area with shelves and some books) (next to the elevator). Walk past the desk and to the left, staying on the first floor. Look to your right for the elevator, it's just past the elevator.
comment: Mostly college kids will be present, but the library is open to anyone. Open until very late at night, opens around 7-8 AM.

name: Seattle Children's Theatre
directions: Up the large grand staircase to the left around a corner.
comment: Only able to use if you are seeing a show at the theatre.

name: Osprey Hall
directions: From parking lot, head into lobby and make an immediate left to a short hallway. Its the first door on the left
comment: Hall doors have special locks so you cannot open the doors without a key card. However, most times people are in the lobby hanging out and will be willing to open the door for anyone without a card or you can wait a moment to see if anyone enters or exits

name: Bubble Tea Express

name: Sweet Pea Cafe

comment:
Wheelchair accessible. There is an all-inclusive sign on the door indicating that all sex/gender identities are welcome.
Hours: Tuesday - Friday: 11:00 am - 8:00 pm
Saturday - Sunday: 11:00 am - 4:00 pm
NO MONDAY

name: CWRU Mandel School of Applied Social Sciences
directions:
Third floor bathrooms near the elevators are multi-stall with privacy details (i.e. no gaps in the door) and are entirely gender-neutral. 
There are gender-neutral private (single) bathrooms at the end of the faculty wing hall on each of the 3 floors (to the left if you are facing the front desk).
comment: Open to members of CWRU and any public using the building for events or work. The building is access-card only outside of normal business hours (8-6 pm M-F).

All floors got many Bathroom and some of them are unisex

Tout les étages ont des WC et certaines sont unisex

name: First Christian Church Cuyahoga Falls
directions: Enter at Stow Ave door by mailbox, turn left in lobby through double doors then immediately on right is bathrooms.
comment: Generally open during week 10am-4pm and all morning Sunday starting around 8:30am. Door is locked so ring buzzer to alert office staff. Just ask to use restroom. We're an open and affirming church and are working to be as intentionally hospitable as possible. Restroom is gender neutral and has changing table and is accessible. :)

name: Super Target CVS Pharmacy
directions: A single-person bathroom just to the left of the pharmacy counter in the middle of the store. If you enter Target at the west (left side) entrance, it's a straight shot back.

name: First Christian Church Cuyahoga Falls

comment: Generally open during week 10am-4pm. Door is locked so ring buzzer to alert office staff. Just ask to use restroom. We're an open and affirming church and are working to be as intentionally hospitable as possible. Restroom is gender neutral and has changing table and is accessible. :)

directions: The west door to the building is always locked, so you have to enter from the east door that faces Eisenhower Hall. There are two accessible single stall unisex bathrooms down the first (and only) hall to the left of the front desk.
comment: When you enter, you'll be face to face with the office staff of the tutoring center. Ignore them and they'll ignore you (but I expect they would be accommodating if you asked where the restrooms are). Just head left around the circle of chairs, the bathrooms are in plain sight but are unmarked white doors. Make sure to close the door all the way to get it to lock properly.
